      Text:
        m_Untranslated: '<a href="https://youtu.be/QpVlVEiOIJ8">Example Video</a>




          With
          our blend tree set up, we now have to transition from locomotion to pivot.


          Go
          back to the Base Layer. Right click "Locomotion", select "Make Transition"
          and drag the arrow towards "Pivot". Do this 2 times! The transition will
          show up as 3 arrows to signal that it contains multiple transitions.


          Select
          the transition. At the top is a list called "Transitions". Make sure the
          first one is selected, then:

          - Deselect "Has Exit Time",

          -
          Set "Transition Duration (s)" to something like 0.05,

          - Add
          the condition "Pivot" "Less" "-0.45".


          Then, select the second
          one and:

          - Deselect "Has Exit Time",

          - Set "Transition
          Duration (s)" to something like 0.05,

          - Add the condition "Pivot"
          "Greater" "0.45".


          Having both these transitions in place will
          transition locomotion into pivot either when we want to turn 45% to the
          left or 45% to the right, while keeping our animator nice and organized.




          If
          you play now and try to pivot, our character will pivot! However, after
          that, they will stand completely still. The next page add transitions to
          address that.'
